'''马萨诸塞大道'''（Massachusetts Avenue）是[[华盛顿哥伦比亚特区|华盛顿哥伦比亚特区]]的一条主要干道和历史街区。

在朗方规划中，马萨诸塞大道穿越华盛顿四个象限中的三个。<ref>L'Enfant identified himself as "Peter Charles L'Enfant" during most of his life, while residing in the United States.  He wrote this name on his [http://hdl.loc.gov/loc.gmd/g3850.ct000512 "Plan of the city intended for the permanent seat of the government of t(he) United States ...."] {{Wayback|url=http://hdl.loc.gov/loc.gmd/g3850.ct000512|date=20160111230315}} (Washington, D.C.) and on other legal documents. However, during the early 1900s, a French ambassador to the United States, [[Jean_Jules_Jusserand|Jean Jules Jusserand]], popularized the use of L'Enfant's birth name, "Pierre Charles L'Enfant". (Reference: Bowling, Kenneth R. (2002). ''Peter Charles L'Enfant: Vision, Honor, and Male Friendship in the Early American Republic''. George Washington University, Washington, D.C. ISBN 978-0-9727611-0-9). The United States Code states in [http://vlex.com/vid/19241289 40 U.S.C. 3309]: "(a) In General.—The purposes of this chapter shall be carried out in the District of Columbia as nearly as may be practicable in harmony with the plan of Peter Charles L'Enfant." The [[National_Park_Service|National Park Service]] identifies L'Enfant as [http://www.nps.gov/history/nr/travel/Wash/text.htm#washington Major Peter Charles L'Enfant] {{Wayback|url=http://www.nps.gov/history/nr/travel/Wash/text.htm#washington|date=20140405134623}} and as [http://www.nps.gov/history/Nr/travel/presidents/washington_monument.html Major Pierre (Peter) Charles L'Enfant] {{Wayback|url=http://www.nps.gov/history/Nr/travel/presidents/washington_monument.html|date=20100228094032}} on its website.</ref>它穿过每一条重要南北街道，经过无数地标。它本身也是一个地标，长期被视为市中心的北部边界以及华盛顿特区使馆区的所在地。

马萨诸塞大道和南侧的[[宾夕法尼亚大道|宾夕法尼亚大道]]两条大道平行，穿过大部分城市，是特区最宽的道路，宽达{{convert|160|ft|m}}。 麻萨诸塞州大道一直是华盛顿首屈一指的住宅街区，而宾夕法尼亚大道是知名的商业街区。 两条街道均以在美国革命中扮演重要角色的州命名：[[麻薩諸塞州|马萨诸塞州]]和[[宾夕法尼亚州|宾夕法尼亚州]]。

马萨诸塞大道历史街区面积{{convert|81|acre|adj=on}}，包括150栋建筑。1985年列入[[国家史迹名录|国家史迹名录]]。<ref name=nris/>

